<body>
<%- await include('partials/navbar.ejs') -%>
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col">
<h1>Jewish Holiday downloads <small class="text-body-secondary">for desktop, mobile and web calendars</small></h1>

<p class="lead">Free Jewish holidays for Microsoft
Outlook, iPhone, iPad, macOS Desktop Calendar, Android (via Google Calendar),
or to any desktop program that supports
iCalendar (.ics) files.</p>
<p>Expand the sections below to download/subscribe in your device or web/desktop
application. Subscribers to these feeds receive perpetual updates.</p>
<p class="small">We provide step-by-step instructions for importing into
<a href="/home/category/import/ios">Apple</a>,
<a href="/home/category/import/google">Google</a>,
<a href="/home/category/import/outlook">Outlook</a> and
<a href="/home/category/import">other calendar apps</a>.</p>
</div><!-- .col -->
</div><!-- .row -->
<div class="row">
<div class="col">
<div class="accordion" id="holidays">
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  titleName: 'Jewish Holidays (only major holidays)',
  name: 'Jewish Holidays', id: 'jewish-holidays-v2',
  emoji: '✡️',
  summary: `<p>Major holidays such as Rosh Hashana, Yom Kippur, Passover, Hanukkah.
<br>Does NOT include minor &amp; modern holidays, fast days or Rosh Chodesh.</p>
<p>Diaspora schedule (for Jews living anywhere outside of modern Israel)</p>`,
  feedLength: '~40',
  years: 10,
  noCSV: true,
  moreInfo: `<p>Without emoji:</p>` + await include('partials/ical-toolbar.ejs', {name: 'Jewish Holidays', basename: 'jewish-holidays'}),
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  titleName: 'Jewish Holidays (all holidays)',
  name: 'Jewish Holidays (all)', id: 'jewish-holidays-all-v2',
  emoji: '✡️ 🌒 🌳 🎭️ 🔥',
  summary: `<p>Major, minor, modern Israeli holidays, fast days and more.
<br>Diaspora schedule (for Jews living anywhere outside of modern Israel)</p>
<ul>
<li>Major holidays such as Rosh Hashana, Yom Kippur, Passover, Hanukkah</li>
<li>Rosh Chodesh</li>
<li>Minor holidays
<span title="Tu BiShvat, Purim Katan, Shushan Purim, Pesach Sheni, Lag BaOmer, Tu B'Av, &amp; Leil Selichot" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-animation="false" data-bs-placement="top"><svg class="icon icon-sm mt-1"><use xlink:href="${spriteHref}#bi-info-circle-fill"></use></svg></span>
</li>
<li>Fast days
<span title="Ta'anit Esther, Tzom Gedaliah, Tzom Tammuz, Asara B'Tevet, &amp; Ta'anit Bechorot" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-animation="false" data-bs-placement="top"><svg class="icon icon-sm mt-1"><use xlink:href="${spriteHref}#bi-info-circle-fill"></use></svg></span>
</li>
<li>Modern Israeli holidays
<span title="Yom HaShoah, Yom HaZikaron, Yom HaAtzma'ut, Yom Yerushalayim, Sigd, &amp; Yom HaAliyah" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-animation="false" data-bs-placement="top"><svg class="icon icon-sm mt-1"><use xlink:href="${spriteHref}#bi-info-circle-fill"></use></svg></span>
</li>
<li>Special Shabbatot
<span title="Shabbat Shuva, Shirah, Shekalim, Zachor, Parah, HaChodesh, HaGadol, Chazon, &amp; Nachamu" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-animation="false" data-bs-placement="top"><svg class="icon icon-sm mt-1"><use xlink:href="${spriteHref}#bi-info-circle-fill"></use></svg></span>
</li>
</ul>`,
  feedLength: '~95',
  years: 8,
  noCSV: true,
  moreInfo: `<p>Without emoji:</p>` + await include('partials/ical-toolbar.ejs', {name: 'Jewish Holidays (all)', basename: 'jewish-holidays-all'}),
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Torah Readings (Diaspora)', id: 'torah-readings-diaspora',
  emoji: '🕍',
  summary: '<p>Parashat ha-Shavua - Weekly Torah Portion such as Bereshit, Noach, Lech-Lecha.</p><p>Diaspora schedule</p>',
  feedLength: '~50',
  years: 5,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'פרשת השבוע - ישראל', id: 'torah-readings-israel-he',
  he: true,
  emoji: '🕍',
  summary: `Parashat ha-Shavua - Weekly Torah Portion such as <span lang="he" dir="rtl">בראשית, נח, לך־לך</span>.</p>
<p>Israel schedule 🇮🇱</p>`,
  feedLength: '~50',
  years: 5,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Hebrew calendar dates (English)', id: 'hdate-en',
  summary: `<p>Displays the Hebrew date (such as <strong class="text-nowrap text-burgundy">18th of Tevet</strong>) every day of the week. Sephardic transliteration.</p>
<p>Hebrew year is included in event title on the 1st of each month (e.g. <strong class="text-nowrap text-burgundy">1st of Kislev, 5782</strong>)</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Hebrew calendar dates (Hebrew)', id: 'hdate-he-v2',
  summary: `<p>Displays the Hebrew date without nikud (e.g. <span lang="he" dir="rtl" class="text-nowrap text-burgundy">י״ח טבת</span>) every day of the week.</p>
<p>Hebrew year is included in event title on the 1st of each month (e.g. <span lang="he" dir="rtl" class="text-nowrap text-burgundy">א׳ כסלו תשפ״ב</span>)</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Hebrew calendar dates (Hebrew with nikud)', id: 'hdate-he',
  summary: `<p>Displays the Hebrew date with nikud (e.g. <span lang="he" dir="rtl" class="text-nowrap text-burgundy">י״ח טֵבֵת</span>) every day of the week</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Days of the Omer', id: 'omer',
  emoji: '㊾',
  summary: '<p>7 weeks from the second night of Pesach to the day before Shavuot</p>',
  feedLength: 49,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Rosh Chodesh', id: 'rosh-chodesh',
  emoji: '🌒',
  summary: `<p>Rosh Chodesh is a minor holiday observed at the beginning of every month in the Hebrew calendar, marked by the birth of a new moon.</p>`,
  feedLength: 18,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Yizkor', id: 'yizkor-diaspora',
  emoji: '🕯️',
  summary: `<p>Ashkenazi Jewish memorial prayer service for the dead recited in synagogue during four holidays yearly.
Diaspora schedule.</p>
<ul>
<li>Yom Kippur</li>
<li>Shmini Atzeret</li>
<li>Pesach: 8th day</li>
<li>Shavuot: 2nd day</li>
</ul>`,
  feedLength: 4,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Yom Kippur Katan', id: 'yom-kippur-katan',
  summary: `<p><span lang="he" dir="rtl">יוֹם כִּפּוּר קָטָן</span> is a minor day of atonement occurring monthly on the day preceding each Rosh Chodesh.</p>
<p class="small">Yom Kippur Katan is omitted in Elul (on the day before Rosh Hashanah),
Tishrei (Yom Kippur has just passed), Kislev (due to Chanukah) or Nisan (fasting not permitted during Nisan).
When Rosh Chodesh occurs on Shabbat or Sunday, Yom Kippur Katan is observed on the preceding
Thursday.&nbsp;<sup><a class="outbound" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yom_Kippur_Katan#Practices">[1]</a></sup></p>`,
  feedLength: 9,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Special Dates on the Chabad Chassidic Calendar', id: 'chabad-special-dates',
  summary: `<p>A perpetual feed of
<a href="https://www.chabad.org/library/article_cdo/aid/357752/jewish/Special-Dates-on-the-Chabad-Chassidic-Calendar.htm">special
dates on the Chabad Chassidic Calendar</a>, including birthdays
and yahrzeits.</p>`,
  feedLength: 23,
  years: 20,
  parent: 'holidays',
}) -%>
</div><!-- .accordion -->
</div><!-- .col -->
</div><!-- .row -->
<div class="row mt-4" id="learning">
<div class="col">
<h3>Daily Learning 📖</h3>
<p>From ancient biblical times, the Torah has been divided into portions which are read each week on a yearly calendar.
In line with this tradition, various calendars have emerged to facilitate groups of learners in collectively studying designated texts.</p>
<div class="accordion" id="learning2">
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Daf Yomi', id: 'daf-yomi',
  summary: `<p>Daily regimen of learning the Babylonian Talmud. This cycle takes approximately
7½ years to complete.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Mishna Yomi', id: 'mishna-yomi',
  summary: `<p>A program of daily learning in which participants study two Mishnayot
each day in order to finish the entire Mishnah in ~6 years.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 5,
  moreInfo: `<p>One chapter per day:</p>` + await include('partials/ical-toolbar.ejs', {name: 'Perek Yomi', basename: 'perek-yomi'}),
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Nach Yomi', id: 'nach-yomi',
  summary: `<p>A daily regimen of learning the books of Nevi'im
(Prophets) and Ketuvim (Writings). This cycle takes ~2 years to complete.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Tanakh Yomi', id: 'tanakh-yomi',
  summary: `<p>A daily learning cycle for completing Tanakh annually.
    On Shabbat, each Torah portion is recited.
    On weekdays, Prophets and Writings are recited according to the ancient Masoretic
division of sedarim. This cycle is completed each year.</p>`,
  feedLength: '~293',
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Daily Tehillim (Psalms)', id: 'psalms',
  summary: `<p>Daily study of a few chapters from the 150-chapter book of Psalms (Tehillim).
The entire book is completed on the final day of each Hebrew month.
On months with 29 days, the 30th portion is combined with the 29th portion.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 2,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Yerushalmi Yomi (Vilna)', id: 'yerushalmi-vilna',
  summary: `<p>Daily regimen of learning the Jerusalem Talmud (Vilna Edition).
Using the Vilna edition, the Yerushalmi Daf Yomi program takes 4¼ years to complete.
Unlike the Daf Yomi Bavli cycle, this Yerushalmi cycle skips both Yom Kippur and Tisha B'Av.</p>`,
  feedLength: 363,
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Yerushalmi Yomi (Schottenstein)', id: 'yerushalmi-schottenstein',
  summary: `<p>Daily regimen of learning the Jerusalem Talmud (Schottenstein Edition).
The Schottenstein edition of Yerushalmi Daf Yomi uses different page numbers
than the Vilna and takes 5¾ years to complete.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Daily Rambam', id: 'rambam1',
  summary: `<p>A learning program that divides Maimonides’ Mishneh Torah legal code
    into daily units, to complete the whole work in three years.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 5,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Daily Chofetz Chaim', id: 'chofetz-chaim',
  summary: `<p>Daily study of the Sefer Chofetz Chaim, which deals with the
Jewish ethics and laws of speech. The book is divided into 119 parts in a regular
year and 129 parts in a leap year.</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Daf-a-Week', id: 'daf-weekly',
  summary: `<p>A learning program that covers a page of Talmud a week.
By going at a slower pace, it facilitates greater mastery and retention.</p>`,
  feedLength: 52,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Pirkei Avot', id: 'pirkei-avot',
  summary: `<p>Pirkei Avot (“Ethics of the Fathers”), studied one chapter
on each Shabbat of the summer between Passover and Rosh Hashanah,
the entire cycle repeating a few times with doubling of chapters
at the end if there are not a perfect multiple of six weeks.</p>`,
  feedLength: 22,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Arukh HaShulchan Yomi', id: 'ahs-yomi',
  summary: `<p>Daily study of the Arukh HaShulchan Yomi, a work
of halacha written by Yechiel Michel Epstein. The work attempts
to be a clear, organized summary of the sources for each chapter
of the Shulchan Arukh and its commentaries, with special emphasis
on the positions of the Jerusalem Talmud and Maimonides</p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 3,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
<%- await include('partials/ical-accordion-item.ejs', {
  name: 'Kindness A Day', id: 'kindness',
  summary: `<p><a href="https://www.areyvut.org/">Areyvut</a>’s daily act of kindness and related quotation from Tanach or Rabbinic text.</p>
<p class="small">Example (February 11): <strong>Visit residents of nursing homes who have no family to visit them.</strong>
<em>"The path of the righteous is like a ray of light" (Proverbs 4:18).</em></p>`,
  feedLength: 365,
  years: 10,
  parent: 'learning2',
}) -%>
</div><!-- .accordion -->
</div><!-- .col -->
</div><!-- .row -->
<div class="row mt-4" id="lang">
<div class="col">
<h3>Customize and download 🌐 🕯️✨ 🇮🇱</h3>
<p>Create and download a custom calendar with event titles in different languages,
<strong>candle-lighting times</strong> for Shabbat and holidays,
<strong>Israeli holiday schedule</strong>, etc</p>
Select an event language:
<ul>
<% for (const [langName, desc] of Object.entries(langNames)) { %>
<li><a href="/hebcal?lg=<%=langName%>"><%=desc[0].replace('transliterations','translit')%></a> <span class="text-body-secondary">- <%=desc[1]||desc[0]%></span></li>
<% } %>
</ul>
</div><!-- .col -->
</div><!-- .row -->
